<article class="env-theorem" id="006H">
  <p><a class="environment-identifier" href="/tag/006H">Theorem <span data-tag="006H">9.3.1</span>.</a> Let $A$ be an algebra considered as an object in $\mathbf{Alg}$. Then defining adjunction data for $\operatorname{ev}_ A\dashv \operatorname{coev}_ A$ is equivalent to defining on $A$ a structure of a symmetric Frobenius algebra. </p>
</article>